-- 
2011-07-26T09:15:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/indian-utilities-quarterly-coal-use-rises-7-india-coal-says.html
Coal consumption by  India â€™s power
utilities rose 7 percent to 98.24 million metric tons in the
quarter ended June 30, India Coal Market Watch said in a note,
citing provisional data by the Central Electricity Authority.  Power companies received 30.24 million tons in June
compared with 30.1 million a year earlier, according to the
note. Imported coal last month climbed to 3.4 million tons from
2.07 million a year earlier. Domestic supplies fell in June, it
